The presidency has said that President Muhammadu Buhari will on Sunday address Nigerians in a live broadcast at 7pm on Sunday. This was announced via the official twitter handle of the Presidency on Sunday. The tweet read: “President @MBuhari will broadcast to the nation Sunday, March 29, 2020 at 7pm. “The president will be addressing the country on Nigeria Television Authority (NTA and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) and other media platforms are urged to hook up with NTA and FRCN. “Television, radio and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (@NTANewsNow) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively for the broadcast.” This development is coming after many Nigerians have criticised President Buhari over his inability to publicly address Nigerians on the COVID-19 pandemic.